                                                                            <comments>
                            <comment id="230813" author="pjones" created="Tue, 24 Jul 2018 13:52:27 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Task completed&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="228106" author="ofaaland" created="Thu, 17 May 2018 20:31:01 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Just to clarify, I meant I didn&apos;t review patches I felt unqualified to review.  Not that I have any concerns about the patches.&lt;br/&gt;
thanks&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="228090" author="ofaaland" created="Thu, 17 May 2018 15:24:57 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi Peter and Bob,&lt;br/&gt;
I see the tests passed on &lt;a href=&quot;https://review.whamcloud.com/#/c/32298&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://review.whamcloud.com/#/c/32298&lt;/a&gt; .  I reviewed the related patches I&apos;m comfortable with, but several still need reviews.  Can you beat the bushes for some reviewers?  Thanks.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="227813" author="ofaaland" created="Mon, 14 May 2018 16:14:51 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;So I don&apos;t have to keep re-looking for this:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-10897&quot; title=&quot;kernel upgrade [RHEL7.5 3.10.0-862.2.3.el7]&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-10897&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-10897&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; kernel: kernel upgrade RHEL7.5 &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;3.10.0-862.2.3.el7&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;br/&gt;
Branch 	b2_8_fe&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://review.whamcloud.com/#/c/32298&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://review.whamcloud.com/#/c/32298&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="227696" author="ofaaland" created="Fri, 11 May 2018 18:13:26 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;According to my testing, 2.8fe also needs&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://review.whamcloud.com/#/c/21260/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://review.whamcloud.com/#/c/21260/&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-8257&quot; title=&quot;Update error if /etc/mtab is a symlink&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-8257&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-8257&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; utils: fix mtab symlink logic&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;To run on RHEL 7.5&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="227609" author="ofaaland" created="Wed, 9 May 2018 22:57:17 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;While you work on getting ldiskfs built and tested under RHEL 7.5 (we only run servers on x86_64, FWIW), I built and am testing 2.8fe with ZFS backend on RHEL 7.5.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This is my stack at the moment:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;81e5e6c (HEAD) Disable ldiskfs build - temporary&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;e5c02eb &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-10565&quot; title=&quot;Handle some small features in upstream&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-10565&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-10565&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; osd: use readdir while iterate is kabi_extend&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;a6791dc &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-9183&quot; title=&quot;Support for linux 4.9 kernels&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-9183&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-9183&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; libcfs: handle dump_trace() and related callbacks removal&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;041becb &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-4199&quot; title=&quot;Lustre client support for ARM platform&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-4199&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-4199&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; libcfs: add wrapper of dump_trace()&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;5221a23 (tag: 2.8.2_1.chaos) &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-7860&quot; title=&quot;LustreError: 19445:0:(ldlm_lock.c:2273:ldlm_lock_cancel()) ASSERTION( !(((( lock))-&amp;gt;l_flags &amp;amp; (1ULL &amp;lt;&amp;lt; 53)) != 0) ) failed&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-7860&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-7860&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; ldlm: revert part of commit 657bbc49&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;Which builds, and is at least minimally functional, but may well not be fully correct.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="227331" author="ofaaland" created="Fri, 4 May 2018 15:42:12 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Note this is not optional for us.  Most of our file systems across the center are currently 2.8fe; all are currently running RHEL 7.4 but need to be upgraded to RHEL 7.5 to conform with our security pollicy.  Clients are almost all 2.8fe.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We don&apos;t have any local patches for kernel updates in our stack.  You can see our stack in the lustre-release-fe-llnl project in gerrit, which we push our tags to.  Our current internal 2.8 release is built from 2.8.2_1.chaos.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="227315" author="pjones" created="Fri, 4 May 2018 13:01:34 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Bob&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Can you help with this?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thanks&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Peter&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
